ARBITRAL AWARD

Findings:
The geological data provided in the tender was fundamentally flawed. The contractor's reliance on it was justified per FIDIC physical conditions clauses.
The design changes directed by the government undoubtedly caused delays.

Award:
Claimant is awarded ₹38.45 Crore + 9% interest.
Respondent's counter claims rejected as the delays were beyond the contractor's control.
